parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to safety risks, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: Vehicle won't start or crank
security mode engages for no reason
Passlock system malfunctions
ignition switch corrodes or has defective contacts
vehicle stalls while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause a range of issues, including stalling, faulty brake lights, and malfunctioning accessories, which can lead to safety risks and accidents.
symptoms: Electrical problems
faulty brake lights
malfunctioning accessories
lights on the panel fade in and out
auxiliary outlets malfunction
battery replacement needed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake System Failure (Premature Brake Pad Wear)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake pad wear can lead to reduced braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake pads wear out prematurely
brake pads need to be replaced frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: HVAC System Failure (Fan Motor Resistor & Connector Overheating)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Overheating of the HVAC fan motor resistor and connector can cause a fire hazard, leading to safety risks.
symptoms: HVAC fan motor resistor and connector overheats
melts
and burns.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Light Switch Failure (NHTSA Recall Campaign Number 09V310000)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake light switch can cause the brake lights to malfunction, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake light switch malfunctions
brake lights do not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning defogger system can reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Defogger does not keep windows clear
reducing visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS wheel speed sensor can cause the ABS system to malfunction, leading to unpredictable braking behavior, increased stopping distances, and potentially accidents.
symptoms: The ABS warning light is illuminated
the brake failure light is illuminated
the vehicle's brakes engage unexpectedly
the vehicle vibrates or makes a grinding noise when braking
the brakes are less effective or fail to engage properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the ABS system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to unpredictable braking behavior, increased stopping distances, and potentially accidents.
symptoms: The ABS warning light is illuminated intermittently
the brake failure light is illuminated intermittently
the vehicle's brakes engage unexpectedly
the vehicle vibrates or makes a grinding noise when braking
the brakes are less effective or fail to engage properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The close proximity of the gas and brake pedals can cause the driver's foot to become stuck, leading to loss of control and potentially accidents.
symptoms: The driver's foot becomes stuck between the gas and brake pedals
the driver has difficulty braking or accelerating
the vehicle is involved in an accident due to pedal interference.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Valve Seat and Seal Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine valve seats and seals can cause engine problems, including intermittent stalling, reduced power, and difficulty starting, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine stalling
reduced power
difficulty starting
"Reduced Power" display in the driver information center
engine dies unexpectedly
and will not restart for several minutes.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Intermittent Starting Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and intermittent starting issues can cause the driver to be stranded, which can lead to accidents or other safety hazards.
symptoms: Engine stalling
difficulty starting
engine cranks but does not turn over
anti-theft security system engages
and waiting for 10-20 minutes allows the engine to turn over successfully.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Engine Sensors and Computer System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty engine sensors and computer system can cause the engine to stall, reduce power, and make it difficult to start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Check engine light comes on
error codes P0300 and P0017
replacing sensors and oil filter does not resolve the issue
and the engine is hard to start and idles rough.
